containsStudent(int) - Method in class Node
This method takes in an ID from the user and checks if it is in the tree by checking the whether the node is smaller than or larger than the current nodes ID, allowing the tree to cut off half the potential results with every step
countChildrenLeft(Node) - Method in class Node
Same as countChildrenRight, but works instead if the ID was Larger than the parents ID
countChildrenRight(Node) - Method in class Node
If the ID to remove was smaller than it's parent's ID this method gets called as the parent will still have all of the leftNodes but the rightNodes are at risk of being lost.
